{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"anchor":"Guides"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GUI app or the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI — both backed by the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a future release.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","type":"heading","text":"Creating a VM with the CLI"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","type":"heading","text":"Creating a VM with the GUI"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Spooktacular.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"+","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" button or press ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cmd+N"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a new VM bundle."}]},{"anchor":"Managing-VMs","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CapacityCheck","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"progress. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProvisioningMode"},{"text":" for provisioning strategies and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"doc:Provisioning","type":"text"},{"text":" for detailed guidance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","level":3,"text":"EC2 Mac Setup"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"release. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for the planned architecture.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"],"anchor":"Guides"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"]}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"title":"Machine Learning Workloads","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"title":"Kubernetes Integration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom